issue.title: update to v1.1
issue.body:
I've published it on the app store, so don't worry about that.

Addition: Now vibrates a bit when you win. Solve time tracking and high-scores will be added in 2.0.
Fix: Instead of lighting up all the time, only lights up temporarily when the ball rolls, as if you pressed a button.
Fix: Movement is prioritized properly (if it can either roll up or sideways, it chooses up if you lean up more).
Fix: Duplicate event loops don't appear when you press select again (app used to go into hyperspeed when you pressed select a bunch).Also cleaned up some code behind the scenes.

issue.title: make recursive maze generator use heap instead of stack
issue.body:
the code is kind of silly, but it turns out that beautiful 24kb of ram
is almost all for the heap/program memory, and just 2kb is for the
stack.  thus, faux-heap callstack.
